values:
Just when i thought i was moving miles away from all those heartaches and pain, taadaaaa there it was a big DETOUR sign. I did not asked for it, it just happened...just like that. 

I left my other phone at the office yesterday, i was too disoriented yesterday because of too many work load plus i'm so pissed off with one of my team mates. I reached home past 10 in the evening, took a 5 minute rest, took a shower, set the alarm of my other phone and then doze off, didn't even bother to eat dinner beacuse im dead tired. When the phone's clock finally hit 5:30am (today), there it was his voice recording...it was my alarm tone way back then. Just when i thought i've erased every memory of him on my phone, pictures, message and all...i missed out on that one. That voice recording of him who would always put a smile on my face each morning, ushering me to wake up and prepare myself&nbsp;to work...telling me how much he loves me. &nbsp;It just hit me so hard, didn't even had the strength to went to the office to render over time work. I could feel the nearly healed wound starts to open again, it felt so raw...so fresh and it hurts more than ever.&nbsp;

Oh God help me...
